70.7	Gladys_Knight	Gladys Knight	Gladys Maria Knight (born May 28, 1944), known as the "Empress of Soul", is an American singer-songwriter, actress, businesswoman, humanitarian, and author. She is best known for the hits she recorded during the 1960s and 1970s, for both the Motown and Buddah Records labels, with her group Gladys Knight &amp; the Pips, the most famous incarnation of which also included her brother Merald "Bubba" Knight and her cousins Edward Patten and William Guest.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Gladys_Knight.jpg/220px-Gladys_Knight.jpg
